  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    Process assessment and improvement efforts can focus on one or more areas of concern, referred to as &quot;process areas.&quot;&#xD;
    Other possible terms for this are &quot;discipline&quot; or &quot;domain.&quot;&amp;nbsp; The term &quot;process area&quot; is chosen to avoid&#xD;
    association with any particular taxonomy, recognizing that there are many ways to categorize process concerns.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Process areas are important to process improvement, because they provide focus for assessment and improvement.&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
    There are recognized process areas, such as &quot;configuration management&quot; and &quot;architecture&quot; for which there are&#xD;
    substantial bodies of knowledge describing best practices and standards.&amp;nbsp; In any process improvement effort, it&#xD;
    is&amp;nbsp;important to decide on areas to focus on, and be able to leverage existing knowledge.&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:ContentDescription>
